<task id="010" project="spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>NEW scripts/Rotate-RedisKey.ps1 — safe-window rotation algorithm</title>
    <phase>2: Theme B — Redis key rotation automation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies></dependencies>
    <blocks>011,013,030</blocks>
    <tags>script, azure, devops, rotation, security</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>New PowerShell script + irreversible Azure operations + safety gates required (NFR-05). FULL would also be defensible; STANDARD with empirical-reproduction verification covers it.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Distinct file domain from Phase 1 and Phase 3.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Create NEW `scripts/Rotate-RedisKey.ps1` — idempotent PowerShell script parameterized by environment (`dev`, `staging`, `prod`). Implements the safe-window rotation algorithm: rotate Secondary → update KV (CONN_NEW with Secondary key) → restart BFF → poll `/healthz` for HTTP 200 within 120s → ON SUCCESS rotate Primary → log success to App Insights as `RedisKeyRotation` custom event. ON HEALTHZ FAILURE: rollback (update KV back to CONN_OLD via KV version history; restart BFF; exit non-zero). Reject `prod`/`staging` without explicit `-Force` (NFR-05). Mirror `Deploy-RedisCache.ps1` patterns.</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke infrastructure developer with PowerShell + Az CLI + Azure Cache for Redis familiarity. Apply `script-aware` skill (load `scripts/README.md` first).</role>
  <goal>`Rotate-RedisKey.ps1 -Environment dev -WhatIf` plans without changes; live `-Environment dev` rotation produces 2 KV secret versions + BFF restart + `/healthz` 200 + `customEvent.RedisKeyRotation` with `outcome=success`. Prod/staging without `-Force` exits non-zero.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-07: replaces the historically-slipping 90-day manual key rotation procedure documented in `docs/guides/redis-cache-azure-setup.md` §6. Mirrors `Deploy-RedisCache.ps1` (R1 task 025) for env-safety + idempotency + post-deploy verification patterns. Closes DEF-001 / Issue #462 without paying +$485/mo for ACR Premium Entra ID.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/Rotate-RedisKey.ps1 (NEW)</file>
      <file>scripts/Deploy-RedisCache.ps1 (REFERENCE PATTERN)</file>
      <file>scripts/README.md (CONVENTIONS)</file>
      <file>docs/guides/redis-cache-azure-setup.md (REFERENCE — current manual procedure §6 being replaced)</file>
      <file>tests/manual/RedisValidationTests.ps1 (REUSE — invariant verification)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-07 — full safe-window algorithm with safe partial failure; rollback path mandatory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-05 — reject prod/staging without explicit -Force (mirrors R1 Deploy-RedisCache.ps1).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">KV reference pattern preserved: `@Microsoft.KeyVault(VaultName=...;SecretName=Redis-ConnectionString)`. Script updates the SECRET; App Settings KV reference resolves automatically.</constraint>
    <constraint source="azure-deployment.md">Idempotent; clear error messages; non-zero exit on failure.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Acceptance: -WhatIf plans for all 3 envs without changes; dry-run on dev produces 2 KV secret versions + BFF restart + /healthz 200 + customEvent.RedisKeyRotation with outcome=success.</constraint>
  </constraints>
