  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read Deploy-RedisCache.ps1 for header doc-comment shape, params block, env-safety gate.</step>
    <step order="2">Read scripts/README.md for Spaarke conventions.</step>
    <step order="3">Read redis-cache-azure-setup.md §6 (current manual procedure) so the automation matches expected operator behavior.</step>
    <step order="4">Author Rotate-RedisKey.ps1 with `[CmdletBinding(SupportsShouldProcess)]`. Parameters: `-Environment {dev|staging|prod}`, `-Force`, `-WhatIf`, `-VerboseLog`.</step>
    <step order="5">Env-to-resource mapping: dev → spaarke-bff-redis-dev / KV `spaarke-spekvcert` / App Service `spaarke-bff-dev` / RG `rg-spaarke-dev`. Staging + prod params TBD by operator at task 030 deploy time — script reads from a config block (or pre-flight prompts).</step>
    <step order="6">Pre-flight: verify Redis + KV + App Service exist via `az` queries; verify operator has required permissions (probe `az keyvault secret set --dry-run` equivalent).</step>
    <step order="7">Algorithm step 1: read current connection string from KV (`az keyvault secret show`) — call it CONN_OLD.</step>
    <step order="8">Algorithm step 2: `az redis regenerate-key --key-type Secondary` against target Redis. Build CONN_NEW using the NEW Secondary key.</step>
    <step order="9">Algorithm step 3: `az keyvault secret set` to upsert `Redis-ConnectionString` with CONN_NEW (creates new secret version; App Settings KV reference resolves automatically on next config refresh).</step>
    <step order="10">Algorithm step 4: `az webapp restart` against the BFF App Service.</step>
    <step order="11">Algorithm step 5: poll `https://{bff-host}/healthz` for HTTP 200 with 120s timeout.</step>
    <step order="12">Algorithm step 6 (success): `az redis regenerate-key --key-type Primary` — eliminates the unused old primary.</step>
    <step order="13">Algorithm step 7 (failure): rollback — `az keyvault secret set` with CONN_OLD; restart BFF; exit non-zero with clear message.</step>
    <step order="14">Log every step to App Insights as `RedisKeyRotation` custom event with `outcome`, `environment`, `duration_ms`. Use App Insights ingestion endpoint or `az monitor app-insights events` (or scriptable approach).</step>
    <step order="15">PSScriptAnalyzer pass if configured.</step>
    <step order="16">-WhatIf smoke verification for all 3 envs.</step>
    <step order="17">Update TASK-INDEX 🔲 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>
  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Deploy-RedisCache.ps1 + README + manual procedure</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Rotate-RedisKey.ps1</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">PowerShell -WhatIf execution + PSScriptAnalyzer</tool>
  </tools>
  <outputs>
    <output type="script">scripts/Rotate-RedisKey.ps1 (NEW)</output>
  </outputs>
